abstract: A new survey shows that many teenagers think their parents have an unhealthy relationship with their mobile devices. Do you wish your parents would put down their phones more?
snippet: A new survey shows that many teenagers think their parents have an unhealthy relationship with their mobile devices. Do you wish your parents would put down their phones more?
lead_paragraph: You’ve been on that device for hours. … Ugh, could you look up every once in a while? Put that phone down, now!

abstract: While parents are, of course, worried about their teenagers’ phone use, that concern goes both ways, a new study found.

abstract: A superhero only a mother could love, with Elizabeth Banks as his mother.
snippet: A superhero only a mother could love, with Elizabeth Banks as his mother.
lead_paragraph: A Kansas farm couple is trying to make a baby. The spoons start rattling, the earth moves — but not how you’d think — and the next thing you know they have a son on the brink of adolescence. One night his bed starts shaking — but not how you’d think — and the next thing you know he’s out in the barn scaring the chickens. Also hovering above the ground, speaking in tongues, and throwing vehicles and people through the air.

headline_print_headline: He’s Such a Sweet Little Boy. No, Wait, No, Ahhh!

abstract: Sy Presten, who turns 95 on May 23 in New York, remembers when the publicity business was fun.
snippet: Sy Presten, who turns 95 on May 23 in New York, remembers when the publicity business was fun.
lead_paragraph: Several women were accusing Joseph R. Biden Jr., about to announce he was running for president, of touching them inappropriately. Sy Presten had a newsy item for the gossip columns.

abstract: His critics could be brutal, but he enthralled millions of readers with novels like “The Winds of War,” “The Caine Mutiny” and “Marjorie Morningstar.”
snippet: His critics could be brutal, but he enthralled millions of readers with novels like “The Winds of War,” “The Caine Mutiny” and “Marjorie Morningstar.”
lead_paragraph: Herman Wouk, whose taut shipboard drama “The Caine Mutiny” lifted him to the top of the best-seller lists, where he remained for most of a career that extended past his 100th year thanks to page-turners like “Marjorie Morningstar,” “Youngblood Hawke” and the World War II epics “The Winds of War” and “War and Remembrance,” died early Friday at his home in Palm Springs, Calif. He was 103.

abstract: This week’s main art fairs are a bit pricey, but looking is free (or nearly) at Frieze Sculpture at Rockefeller Center and alternative fairs in Brooklyn and Manhattan.
snippet: This week’s main art fairs are a bit pricey, but looking is free (or nearly) at Frieze Sculpture at Rockefeller Center and alternative fairs in Brooklyn and Manhattan.
lead_paragraph: It’s Frieze Week in New York, which means big-name dealers with top-notch art — and hefty entrance fees. But there are alternative displays opening across the city this week, with modestly priced works by established and emerging artists. (These fairs are easier on the pocket and a little less overwhelming for casual browsers, too.) Here is a guide to some of them.

abstract: Many dating and lifestyle consultants are divorced women who want to provide the kind of guidance they found lacking when they were starting over.
snippet: Many dating and lifestyle consultants are divorced women who want to provide the kind of guidance they found lacking when they were starting over.
lead_paragraph: About five years ago, Joe Ragusa, a city Sanitation employee who works in the Bronx, got fed up with traffic and construction and all the other stuff and decided to move out of the city. He bought a house in the country, in the hamlet of Mahopac, and moved in with his girlfriend. Naturally, they broke up.

abstract: As dominant as Sabathia was early in his career, he has piled up statistics worthy of the Hall of Fame by finding a different gear well into his 30s.
snippet: As dominant as Sabathia was early in his career, he has piled up statistics worthy of the Hall of Fame by finding a different gear well into his 30s.
lead_paragraph: The two most similar pitchers to C.C. Sabathia in major league history, according to Baseball Reference, are Andy Pettitte and Mike Mussina, both Yankees stalwarts. Pettitte taught Sabathia the cutter late in his career. Mussina knew he needed it.

lead_paragraph: Almost two years after the Mueller investigation began, the special counsel’s findings, submitted last month, have become public. On Thursday, Attorney General William P. Barr released a redacted version of the more than 400-page report.
